The paper discusses representation learning in the context of imitation learning for Markov decision processes (MDPs), which is a problem commonly studied in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization and control of MDPs, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper includes experiments with image data, suggesting a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
